# ruvllm-bridge — environment template (ADR-173, iter 124).
#
# UNLIKE the other two bridges, ruvllm-bridge is NOT a long-running
# systemd daemon. It's a stdin/stdout JSONL adapter — the parent
# ruvllm process spawns it as a subprocess, pipes JSON requests in,
# reads JSON responses out, and the bridge exits cleanly on EOF.
#
# Consequence: this env file isn't sourced by a systemd unit. Instead,
# the parent process (or the iter-215 install-ruvllm-bridge.sh wrapper)
# uses it to set defaults via `set -a; . file; set +a` before exec'ing
# the bridge with arguments built from the env vars.
#
# All flags below correspond 1:1 to the bridge's CLI surface (run
# `ruvllm-bridge --help` for the canonical list).

# ---- Required ----

# Cluster sink — comma-separated host:port list of the hailo-backend
# workers' gRPC endpoints. Same flag as embed/bench/stats --workers.
RUVECTOR_RUVLLM_WORKERS=100.77.59.83:50051,100.77.59.84:50051

# sha256 hex of the cluster's HEF + vocab. Required by the §2a gate;
# unset means "no enforcement", which the gate refuses unless
# --allow-empty-fingerprint is set.
RUVECTOR_RUVLLM_FINGERPRINT=

# ---- Optional ----

# Embed dimensionality. Defaults to 384 (all-MiniLM-L6-v2). Override
# only if the fleet runs a different model.
RUVECTOR_RUVLLM_DIM=384

# Extra args appended verbatim to the bridge invocation. Useful for:
#   --quiet                   (suppress informational stderr)
#   --allow-empty-fingerprint (legacy fleet without an HEF)
#
# TLS / mTLS (iter 187/188/189 client flags, requires `--features tls`
# on the bridge build):
#   --tls-ca /etc/ruvector-ruvllm/ca.pem
#   --tls-domain hostname     (SNI to assert; default = hostname half
#                              of the first --workers entry. Required
#                              when the workers are addressed by IP
#                              and the cert SAN is a DNS name.)
#   --tls-client-cert /etc/ruvector-ruvllm/client.pem
#   --tls-client-key  /etc/ruvector-ruvllm/client.key
#
# Iter 238/243/245 cluster-side knobs (recommended for RAG deploys):
#   --cache 4096             coordinator-side LRU; ~32500x speedup at
#                            full hit rate. Real ruvllm RAG flows query
#                            the same context strings repeatedly, so
#                            this is the highest-value bridge for cache.
#   --cache-ttl 300          5-min max-staleness bound (use even with
#                            short-lived bridges to bound staleness if
#                            the parent ruvllm process is itself long-
#                            running and reuses one bridge instance).
#   --health-check 30        only useful for long-running bridge sessions;
#                            no-op if ruvllm forks the bridge per-session.
# Typical hardened RAG deploy:
#   RUVECTOR_RUVLLM_EXTRA_ARGS=--cache 4096 --cache-ttl 300
RUVECTOR_RUVLLM_EXTRA_ARGS=
